The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Nov. 9: The Reserve Bank of India has announced special measures to increase money supply in the financial system in a bid to ease liquidity pressure on the banking system because of a spurt in festival season demand. According to the RBIs special measures, banks will be able to get more funds under the liquidity adjustment facility for up to 1 per cent more on their deposits.                             
	 Mumbai, Nov. 9: Market regulator Sebi today said brokers would be responsible for sale and redemption of units being bought by investors from the secondary market. Payment of redemption proceeds to the broker/clearing members by MF/AMC shall discharge MF/AMC of its obligation of payment to individual investor, Sebi said in a circular.                             
	 Mumbai, Nov. 9: Mahindra Satyam will announce its results for the quarters ended June 30 and September 30 according to the Indian accounting standards on November 15. Meanwhile, former Satyam Computer chairman B. Ramalinga Raju has approached the Supreme Court seeking an extension of time beyond November 10 to surrender.                             
	 Hyderabad, Nov. 9: The Insurance Regulatory Authority of India will formulate guidelines for mergers and acquisitions (M amp;A) for non-life insurance companies, Irda chairman J. Harinarayana said.                             
	 Mumbai, Nov. 9: SKS Microfinance will reduce interest rates across states to 24 per cent, after the Andhra Pradesh state government came out with an ordinance to control the micro lenders.
                                                                                                                          
